All Real accounts in balance sheet

ASSETS = LIABILITIES + EQUITY 

Assets = Liabilities + ( Owner's capital + Income - Expenses )

Retained earnings = Income - Expenses

Assets: What you own
Liability: What you owe
Equity: Residuals of company after paying of liabilities (owe)

Nature of Equity is same as liabilities as company owes shares to shareholders

Assets: accounts that will give you future benefit

asset accounts:

current assets:
 cash and cash equivalents
 account receivables
 inventory
 prepaid expense                           #You will receive benefit of prepaid expense in future(asset)
 short term investments
 other current assets

Non current assets:
 property land and equipment
   land
   building 
   machinery
   vehicles
   furniture
   accumulated depreciation : less  # contra asset ( you dont owe to anyone, its natural value drop of )

 intangible assets:
   good will      #same as prepaid expense, but benefit is not guarenteed ( excess paid than asset value)
   patents
   trademarks
   softwares

 long term investments:
   equity investments
   bonds

 tax assets   #money that government owns you from filing returns/advance tax paid
 long term loans and advances  #amounts given to others
 other non current Assets

Liabilities

current liabilities:
 accounts payable
 short term loans
 current portion of long term debt
 accrued expenses   #benefitted on credit, cash not yet flown out , but obliged to pay
 tax payable
 unearned revenue   #company got advance but, the service of this much value amount is yet to be delivered
 other current liabilities

non current liabilities
 long term debt
 lease liabilities
 deferred tax liabilities #you have paid less tax, because tax laws allow it but pay more later
 pension liabilities 
 long term provisions
 other long term liabilities

equity
 share captial
 additional paid in capital
 retained earnings
 other comprehensive income
 tresury stock #buyback shares
 


